tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE warehouse_sensor_data (
	sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	sensor_type VARCHAR(50),
	temperature DECIMAL,
	humidity DECIMAL,
	storage_condition VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE warehouse_sensors (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    sensor_name VARCHAR(50),
    temperature DECIMAL,
    humidity DECIMAL,
    storage_condition VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    sensor_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    temperature DECIMAL,
    humidity DECIMAL,
    storage_condition VARCHAR(100),
    FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES warehouse_sensors(sensor_id)
);

CREATE TABLE warehouse_storage_conditions (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    air_quality VARCHAR,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE warehouse { 
  sensor_id INT, 
  sensor_type VARCHAR(50), 
  temperature FLOAT, 
  humidity FLOAT, 
  timestamp TIMESTAMP, 
  PRIMARY KEY (sensor_id) 
}

CREATE TABLE storage_conditions (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_id INT,
  temperature FLOAT,
  humidity FLOAT,
  air_quality FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE sensor_readings (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  sensor_id INT,
  temperature FLOAT,
  humidity FLOAT,
  air_quality FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
